# HDF5 Dtype Convention

Save compact, load standard.

## Save (HDF5 on disk / `_concat_graph_blocks` return)

| Array type | dtype |
|---|---|
| Integer features / indices (`node_feat`, `edge_feat*`, `edge_index*`) | `uint8` |
| Continuous features (`node_embd`) | `float16` |
| Boundary pointers (`*_ptr`) | `int32` |
| Labels | `float32` |

## Load (`_load_hdf5`)

| Array type | dtype |
|---|---|
| Integer features / indices | `int32` |
| Continuous features | `float32` |
| Boundary pointers (`*_ptr`) | `int32` |
| Labels | `float32` |

## Examples

```python
# ✅ save compact
np.asarray(edge_feat_arr, dtype=np.uint8)   # features
np.asarray(node_embd_arr, dtype=np.float16) # continuous
np.asarray(node_ptr, dtype=np.int32)        # pointer

# ✅ load standard
node_feat = np.asarray(f['node_feat'][()], dtype=np.int32)
node_embd = np.asarray(f['node_embd'][()], dtype=np.float32)
edge_ptr  = np.asarray(f['edge_ptr'][()],  dtype=np.int32)

# ❌ wrong: loading index as uint8
edge_index = np.asarray(f['edge_index'][()], dtype=np.uint8)
```
